16 WHEREAS, complementary therapies such as art, music, and animal-assisted programs have
17 also shown promise in enhancing communication and social engagement for individuals with
18 autism; and
19 WHEREAS, Autism Acceptance Month, observed annually in April, promotes greater
20 understanding and inclusion of individuals with autism, shifting the narrative from awareness
21 to acceptance and fostering more supportive, affirming communities; and
22 WHEREAS, World Autism Awareness Day, held on April 2 each year, provides an
23 international platform to recognize the contributions and rights of individuals with autism as
24 well as to promote global dialogue on inclusivity and support systems.
25 NOW, THEREFORE, BE IT RESOLVED BY THE SENATE that the members of this body
26 recognize April 2025 as Autism Acceptance Month and April 2, 2025, as World Autism
27 Awareness Day as well as commend all organizations, advocates, and families working to
28 create a more inclusive world for individuals with autism.
29 BE IT FURTHER RESOLVED that the Secretary of the Senate is authorized and directed
30 to make appropriate copies of this resolution available for distribution to the public and the
31 press.
